4. Prompt 3 — Developer Usage Guide
Prompt used: Create a friendly developer guide for junior developers explaining authentication, request formatting, response handling, error handling, and Python code examples.

Target audience: Junior developers new to APIs. Tone: Friendly and clear.

What This Endpoint Does
This endpoint lets you create a new user account. You send a username, email, and password — and if everything checks out, you get back a user profile. Think of it as the sign-up form for your application.

Step 1 — Authentication
Good news — this endpoint needs NO authentication. It's how users are created in the first place! However, most other endpoints in this API will require a token after you log in.

Step 2 — Format Your Request
Always send JSON with the Content-Type header set correctly:

import requests

url = 'http://localhost:5000/api/users/register'

payload = {
    "username": "lesego_writes",
    "email": "lesego@example.com",
    "password": "securepass123"
}

headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json"
}

response = requests.post(url, json=payload, headers=headers)
print(response.status_code)
print(response.json())

Step 3 — Handle the Response
Always check the status code first, then read the response body:

if response.status_code == 201:
    user = response.json()['user']
    print(f"Welcome {user['username']}! Your ID is {user['id']}")

elif response.status_code == 409:
    error = response.json()
    print(f"Problem: {error['message']}")

elif response.status_code == 400:
    error = response.json()
    print(f"Check your input: {error['message']}")

else:
    print('Something went wrong on the server — try again later')

Step 4 — Common Errors and Fixes
Error you see	What it means	How to fix it
username is required	Missing field in JSON body	Make sure all three fields are included
Username is already in use	Someone has that username	Try a different username
Password must be at least 8 characters	Password too short	Use a longer password
Please provide a valid email	Email format is wrong	Check for @ symbol and domain
Failed to register user	Server problem	Wait a moment and try again

Things to Know
•	Your email gets stored as lowercase — LESEGO@example.com becomes lesego@example.com
•	You will get a confirmation email after registering — check your inbox
•	Your password is NEVER stored — only a secure hash is saved
•	You will always be assigned role: 'user' when first registering
•	If the confirmation email fails to send, your account is still created successfully

5. Reflections
Most Challenging Parts to Document
•	The silent email failure — confirmation email errors are logged but don't affect the response, which isn't obvious without reading the code carefully
•	The order of validation checks — duplicates are checked before email format, which affects what error a user sees first
•	The rollback behaviour — important for data integrity but easy to miss

